result.name: MegaBox

reviews.text:
Kowloon bay shopping mall, many restaurants and shops 
You can spend a day there.
After shopping, we go to McDonald’s to try a new product ‘cheese series’

Huge retail mall filled with shops and a cinema. I mainly chilled and enjoyed the view outside while reading a book as the school pupils I was with meandered around. I was _just_ too late to book a cinema ticket for the one showing I had the time to see!

Nice to wander around.

If you want to try parking your car on the 16th floor, this is the place for you. 😁 I'd say Megabox is the best shopping mall for car drivers in Hong Kong. It has a huge carpark, going from the basement all the way to the 16th floor (skipping a lot of the story in between thou). There are a huge number of restaurant from 10th floor up and a dozen more below that. There is one of the four ice skating court open to public. There is the IKEA shop taking two stories of the mall. The 9th floor is all about kids stuffs. Aeon takes two floors. You can easily spend half a day here.

There is shuttle bus service from the Kowloon Bay MTR station. It is at the very end of the Telford Plaza phase 2 so it is a bit of a walk. But it is giving free rides to and from the Megabox mall.

Out of the way, bathrooms can be filthy and the store selection (besides IKEA and some other furnishing stores) is quite standard.  Decent selection of restaurants though, a cinema and ice rink. So... if you are looking for somewhere not overly busy (like other malls in the area can be) then this could be the place.
Excellent variety of stores and facilities but lack of a helpdesk can make them difficult to locate
